            "body": "Another use case for this I can think of it's with `clangd`, it supports a remote index server, I work in multiple projects that use different remote indexers, so far now I use `.exrc` to modify clangd command per repo to point to the correct indexer since I haven't find a better way to modify the cmd dynamically without monkey patching `vim.lsp.config` itself, this would do the trick, I would just need a config file and return the corresponding command with the correct indexer depending on the repo.",
